Reading of data

brick_sandiego <- brick('sandiego_test.tif')
names(brick_sandiego) <-  c("ghsl","nldc","imp","tree","ndvi","lts")

Newdataframe form rasterdata

df_sandiego <- as.data.frame(brick_sandiego, xy = TRUE)

xydf <-  df_sandiego %>%
   dplyr::select(x, y) 

dataset <- df_sandiego %>%
   drop_na()

Heuristic Criterion in PCA

matrix_cor <- dataset %>%
   dplyr::select(-c(x,y)) %>% 
   cor()

ggcorrplot(corr = matrix_cor,
           ggtheme = theme_minimal(),
           title = 'Matrix of variables correlation',
           lab = TRUE,
           colors = cpt(pal = 'mpl_viridis',n=3),
           lab_col = 'white')

Test KMO ~ MSA

# (measure of sampling adequacy, MSA >=7)
KMO(r = matrix_cor) 
## Kaiser-Meyer-Olkin factor adequacy
## Call: KMO(r = matrix_cor)
## Overall MSA =  0.6
## MSA for each item = 
## ghsl nldc  imp tree ndvi  lts 
## 0.61 0.65 0.59 0.62 0.60 0.57

Principal Component Analysis

san_diego <- dataset %>%
   dplyr::select(c(-x,-y)) %>% 
   prcomp(scale. = TRUE) 
summary(san_diego)
## Importance of components:
##                           PC1    PC2    PC3    PC4     PC5     PC6
## Standard deviation     1.5048 1.2339 0.9066 0.8251 0.65717 0.52784
## Proportion of Variance 0.3774 0.2537 0.1370 0.1135 0.07198 0.04644
## Cumulative Proportion  0.3774 0.6311 0.7681 0.8816 0.95356 1.00000
# SanDiego => 4PCA >= 80% accumulated variance

Eingvector de PCA

eingvector <- san_diego$rotation[,1:4]
eingvector
##             PC1        PC2        PC3         PC4
## ghsl  0.4716971 -0.3076987 0.25935660 -0.55026983
## nldc -0.4516281  0.2567135 0.39980890 -0.55458123
## imp   0.5558511 -0.2871065 0.05692165 -0.09409047
## tree -0.1925510 -0.5247282 0.58647025  0.51462924
## ndvi -0.4043291 -0.4723998 0.06139105 -0.31293298
## lts   0.2529933  0.5084173 0.64956194  0.13423655

\[PC_{1} = -0.4118xndlc + 0.5161ximp + 0.5161xtree - 0.4063xndvi + 0.0781xtmax + 0.3473xtmin\] \[PC_{2} = 0.1821xndlc + -0.1491ximp + -0.1491xtree +-0.1596xndvi + 0.9071xtmax + 0.2719xtmin\]

\[PC_{3} = -0.3101xndlc +0.1869ximp + 0.1869xtree + + 0.1859xndvi -0.3966 xtmax - -0.8012xtmin\]

pc1 <- eingvector %>% 
   as_tibble() %>%
   mutate(name = rownames(eingvector)) %>% 
   ggplot(aes(x = PC1,
              y = name,
              fill = PC1)) + 
   geom_bar(stat = 'identity',
            color = "black",
            lwd = 0.2,
            alpha = 0.9) +
   scale_fill_continuous_diverging(palette = "Blue-Red 3") +
   theme_minimal() + 
   labs(title = 'PC1-Without rotation varimax',
        x = ' ',
        y = ' ') + 
   theme(legend.position = 'top',
         legend.justification = 'center',
         plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5,
                                   size = 11,
                                   face = 'bold'))

pc2 <- eingvector %>% 
   as_tibble() %>%
   mutate(name = rownames(eingvector)) %>%

Eingvalues de PCA ~ SanDiego

eingvalues <- tibble(
   Components = sprintf('pc%s',1:6),
   variance = san_diego$sdev^2/sum(san_diego$sdev^2)) %>% 
      mutate(accumulated = cumsum(variance))
eingvalues
## # A tibble: 6 x 3
##   Components variance accumulated
##   <chr>         <dbl>       <dbl>
## 1 pc1          0.377        0.377
## 2 pc2          0.254        0.631
## 3 pc3          0.137        0.768
## 4 pc4          0.113        0.882
## 5 pc5          0.0720       0.954
## 6 pc6          0.0464       1

Screen plot

eingvalues %>% 
   ggplot(aes(x = Components,y = variance, group = 1)) +
   geom_bar(stat = 'identity', fill = "#699bff") + 
   geom_line() + 
   geom_point(aes(size = variance))  + 
   theme_minimal() +
   labs(title = 'Screen plot',x = '') +
   theme(legend.position = 'none',
         plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5,
                                   size = 20,

Criterion Kaiser eingvalues > 1

eingvalues_kaiser <- varimax(san_diego$x)
loadings_rot <- eingvalues_kaiser$rotmat %>% 
   as_tibble() %>%
   mutate(name = rownames(eingvector))
names(loadings_rot)[1:6] <- sprintf('rot%s',1:6)

rot1 <- loadings_rot %>% 
   ggplot(aes(x = rot1 ,y = name, fill = rot1)) +

New raster with 3PCA

dataset_pcs <- cbind(dataset,san_diego$x[,1:3])
sandiego_pca <- xydf %>%
   left_join(y = dataset_pcs,by = c('y','x'))

newraster <- sandiego_pca %>%
   dplyr::select(x, y, PC1, PC2, PC3)

Parameters of new raster

sandiego_crs  <- crs(brick_sandiego)
sandiego_res <- res(brick_sandiego)
sandiego_newraster <- rasterFromXYZ(
   newraster,
   sandiego_res,
   sandiego_crs
   )

Export PCA

writeRaster(sandiego_newraster,'./sandiego_pca.tif',overwrite = TRUE)
write.csv(newraster,'./sandiego_pca.csv')

Plot PCA

pc1 <- levelplot(sandiego_newraster$PC1,
          col.regions = cpt('mpl_magma',rev = TRUE),
          main = "PC1",
          margin = FALSE,
          xlab = '',
          ylab = '' ,
          colorkey = list(space = 'bottom')
          )

pc2 <- levelplot(sandiego_newraster$PC2,
          col.regions = cpt('mpl_viridis',rev = TRUE),
          main = "PC2",
          margin = FALSE,
          xlab = '',
          ylab = '' ,
          colorkey = list(space = 'bottom')
          )

pc3 <- levelplot(sandiego_newraster$PC3,
          col.regions = cpt('mpl_plasma'),
          main = "PC3",
          margin = FALSE,
          xlab = '',
          ylab = '' ,
          colorkey = list(space = 'bottom')
          )

plot_grid(pc1, pc2, pc3,rel_widths = c(5,5))

Clustering Analysis

data_cluster <- dataset

Indentifying the best cluster

wss <- 0
for(i in 1:6) {
  # Run kmeans() on x with three clusters and one start
  km.out <- kmeans(data_cluster, centers = i, nstart = 20)
  wss[i] <- km.out$tot.withinss
}

wss %>% 
  as_tibble(wss = wss) %>%
  mutate(ncluster = 1:n()) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = ncluster, y = value)) +
  geom_bar(stat = 'identity', fill = '#580a94') + 
  geom_point(aes(size = value)) + 
  geom_line() +
  theme_minimal() + 
  theme(legend.position = 'none') + 
  labs(x = 'Number of cluster', y = 'Within groups sum of squares')

Add new values of cluster

km_out <- kmeans(data_cluster, centers = 3, nstart = 20)

cluster_newdata <- cbind(dataset,km_out$cluster)
sandiego_cluster <- xydf %>%
  left_join(y = cluster_newdata,
            by = c('y','x')) %>% 
  dplyr::select(x, y, `km_out$cluster`)

Mapping cluster

sandiego_crs  <- crs(brick_sandiego)
sandiego_res <- res(brick_sandiego)
cluster_sd <- rasterFromXYZ(
  sandiego_cluster,
  res = sandiego_res,
  crs = sandiego_crs) %>% 
  raster::as.factor()

Plot cluster

levelplot(cluster_sd$km_out.cluster,
          col.regions = cpt(pal = 'mpl_viridis',3),
          main = "Kmean - cluster",
          margin = FALSE,
          xlab = '',
          ylab = '' ,
          colorkey = list(space = 'bottom')
          )
